
SOURCE

http://www.newsweek.com/prevent-heart-disease-and-stroke-just-drinking-coffee-709807?yptr=yahoo

AGENT

Laura M. Stevens of University of Colorado and other researchers.

GOAL

Assessing the health effects of different eating habits, especially heart related health effects.

DATA

They used data from the long-running Framingham Heart Study, which contains information about the participants' eating habits and their health.

METHODS

Random decision forests were used to find correlations between different eating habits and health conditions. 

RESULTS

Drinking coffee was linked to a 7 percent decrease in heart failure and an 8 percent decrease in stroke for every cup drunk per week.

COMMENTS

Correlation doesn't imply causation.
